Explanation of abbreviations:

Solvents: EtOH=ethanol, i-PrOH=isopropanol, MeOH=methanol
Mechanism: S1=substitution on reducable heterocyclic ring, S2=substitution on
benzene ring annelated to reducable heterocyclic ring and simultaneous reduction
on both rings, S3=substitution on phenyl ring bonded to reducable heterocyclic
ring, change of rings bonded to heterocyclic ring, S4=influence of substitution
in benzene ring on reduction in the neighbouring chain on heterocyclic ring
Oxidation or reduction: O=oxidation, R=reduction
Potentials: EH=parental derivative (all R´s=H), E=desired derivative
